# 🧠 Step 1: Create Linear Regression Service (Node.js)

We’ll use a **simple formula**:
[
y = mx + c
]

### 📁 Project Structure

```
lr-service/
 ├── server.js
 ├── package.json
 └── Dockerfile
```

---

### 📄 `package.json`

```json
{
  "name": "lr-service",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "main": "server.js",
  "dependencies": {
    "express": "^4.18.2"
  }
}
```

---

### 📄 `server.js`

```js
const express = require("express");
const app = express();
app.use(express.json());

// Example trained model values
const m = 2;   // slope
const c = 1;   // intercept

app.get("/", (req, res) => {
  res.send("Linear Regression Service Running 🚀");
});

app.post("/predict", (req, res) => {
  const x = req.body.value;

  if (x === undefined) {
    return res.status(400).json({ error: "Please provide value" });
  }

  const y = m * x + c;

  res.json({
    input: x,
    prediction: y
  });
});

app.listen(3000, () => {
  console.log("Server running on port 3000");
});
```

